{"timestamp": "2026-03-19T17:06:05.227417", "elapsed_seconds": 23.96, "stage": "INFO", "message": "Generated response from Gemini", "data": {"response": "To start a new FastAPI project, you have a couple of approaches based on the provided documentation:\n\n1.  **Using a Template:**\n    You can use the \"Full Stack FastAPI Template\" which is designed to help you get started quickly, as it includes initial setup, security, database, and some API endpoints already done for you. (Document 6)\n\n2.  **Manual Setup:**\n    *   Create an `app` directory. (Document 1)\n    *   Inside the `app` directory, create an empty file named `__init__.py`. (Document 1)\n    *   Create a `main.py` file within the `app` directory. In this file, you would:\n        *   Import `FastAPI`. (Document 1, Document 11)\n        *   Create an `app` instance, for example: `app = FastAPI()`. (Document 1, Document 11)\n        *   Define path operation decorators (e.g., `@app.get(\"/\")`) and path operation functions (e.g., `def root(): ...`). (Document 11)\n    *   To run your development server, you can use the command `fastapi dev`. (Document 11, Document 21) You can also specify the file path, for example, `fastapi dev main.py`. (Document 16)", "response_length": 1066, "tokens_used": 161, "sources_extracted": ["Source: docs\\deployment\\docker.md", "Source: docs\\project-generation.md", "Source: docs\\tutorial\\first-steps.md", "Source: docs\\fastapi-cli.md"]}}
